The body of a fashion designer who went missing in March was found in the water by police on Thursday.

Police discovered the body of James 'Jay' Ott, 31, around 11:10am floating near Sunset Park's Pier 4, police said in a Thursday statement.

His body was taken to the bay and was pronounced dead on arrival, police said in the statement.

Ott's body was identified on Friday, police said.

Police said the cause of death has yet to be determined and that they continue to investigate.

