Ott went missing in March and worked for fashion design company the Dock Group, according to a report by The Cut. He earlier worked for J.Mendel and The Row, the latter of which is a fashion brand established by Mary Kate and Ashley Olsen.

That report said Ott was last seen on March 23 surveillance footage at the Williamsburg Bridge at 5:02am, after he had already left his Bushwick apartment and gone to a bodega. Loved ones reportedly organized a search for him, under the group name Friends of Jay Ott.

A since-deleted March 26 tweet from Elizabeth and James, another Olsen fashion brand, also encouraged the search for Ott.

'please spread the word RT@Fashionista_com MISSING: Where is NYC fashion designer Jay Ott? ' it read, according to Perez Hilton.

Police told the New York Daily News in March that Ott suffered from anxiety.

